<inglise> REGULATION (EEC) No 2750/75 OF THE COUNCIL of 29 October 1975 fixing criteria for the mobilization of cereals intended as food aid </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 2750/75, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks toiduabiks etten&auml;htud teravilja varumise kriteeriumid 29. oktoober 1975 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75 (1) of 29 October 1975 on the common organization of the market in cereals, and in particular Article 28 thereof: </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. oktoobri 1975. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 (1) teraviljaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, eriti selle artiklit 28, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation No 359/67/EEC (2) of 25 July 1967 on the common organization of the market in rice, as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 668/75 (3), and in particular Article 23a thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 25. juuli 1967. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust nr 359/67/EM&Uuml; (2) riisituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 668/75, (3) eriti selle artiklit 23a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulations (EEC) No 2727/75 and No 359/67/EEC provide in their Articles 28 and 23a respectively for the Council to fix the criteria according to which products intended as food aid must be mobilized on the Community market; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;rustega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 ja nr 359/676/EM&Uuml; n&auml;hakse ette vastavalt artiklites 28 ja 23a, et n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks kriteeriumid, mille kohaselt toiduabiks m&otilde;eldud tooteid tuleb &uuml;henduse turul varuda; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas disturbance of the market in cereals caused by withdrawals of cereals intended as food aid should be avoided; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks v&auml;ltida h&auml;ireid teraviljaturul, mida p&otilde;hjustab toiduabiks m&otilde;eldud teravilja turult k&otilde;rvaldamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the possibility should be provided for cereals to be mobilized in Community regions in order to relieve the regional market, when the market situation in those regions is likely to cause intervention agencies to buy in large quantities of cereals; whereas, when certain intervention agencies hold quantities of cereals, mobilization of all or part of the cereals held by them may help to improve their situation; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks ette n&auml;ha v&otilde;imalus varuda teravilja &uuml;henduse piirkondades, et leevendada olukorda piirkondlikul turul, kui sekkumisametid peaksid sealsest olukorrast tingituna suuri teraviljakoguseid kokku ostma; kui teatavate sekkumisametite valduses on suured teraviljavarud, v&otilde;ib kogu v&otilde;i osa nende valduses oleva teravilja varumine aidata olukorda parandada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, when such specific cases do not arise, cereals should be mobilized on the Community market as a whole; </inglise>
<eesti> kui selliseid konkreetseid juhte ei esine, tuleks teravilja varuda &uuml;henduse turul tervikuna; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the procedure of issuing invitations to tender best enables cereals to be effectively mobilized; whereas for emergency operations, however, it may be decided to use different procedures for the sake of speed, </inglise>
<eesti> pakkumismenetlus v&otilde;imaldab teravilja k&otilde;ige tulemuslikumalt varuda; kriisiolukorras v&otilde;ib siiski otsustada kasutada kiiruse huvides teistsuguseid menetlusi, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation "cereals" shall be products referred to: (a) in Article 1 of Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75; </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamisel t&auml;hendab "teravili" j&auml;rgmistes m&auml;&auml;rustes osutatud tooteid: a) m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 artikkel 1, </eesti>
<inglise> (b) in Article 1 of Regulation No 359/67/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> b) m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 359/67/EM&Uuml; artikkel 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Cereals intended as food aid shall be mobilized on the Community market in accordance with the following provisions. </inglise>
<eesti> Toiduabiks m&otilde;eldud teravili varutakse &uuml;henduse turul vastavalt j&auml;rgmistele s&auml;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> When, in a Community region, trends in cereal market prices register a decline or slump which, in view of the volume of the harvest or of regional stocks and their geographical situation, is likely to force the intervention agency to buy in large quantities of cereals, cereals may be bought in on the market of the region concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui m&otilde;nes &uuml;henduse piirkonnas n&auml;itavad teravilja turuhindade arengusuunad kahanemist v&otilde;i &auml;kklangust, mis koristusmahtu v&otilde;i piirkondlikke varusid ja nende geograafilist olukorda silmas pidades sunnib t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt sekkumisametit suuri teraviljakoguseid kokku ostma, v&otilde;ib teravilja osta asjaomase piirkonna turult. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> When an intervention agency holds stocks these stocks may be used. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui sekkumisameti valduses on varusid, v&otilde;ib neid kasutada. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> When the conditions referred to in paragraph 1 or 2 are not fulfilled or when use is not made of the possibilities provided for in those paragraphs, cereals shall be bought in on the Community market as a whole. (1) See page 1 of this Official Journal. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 osutatud tingimused ei ole t&auml;idetud v&otilde;i kui ei kasutata nimetatud l&otilde;igetega etten&auml;htud v&otilde;imalusi, ostetakse teravilja &uuml;henduse turult tervikuna. </eesti>
<inglise> (2) OJ No 174, 31.7.1967, p. 1. (3) OJ No L 72, 20.3.1975, p. 18. </inglise>

<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The buying in operations referred to in Article 3 (1) and (3) shall be carried out by the intervention agencies by inviting tenders for the supply of the product delivered either fob or at a corresponding stage. </inglise>
<eesti> Sekkumisametid sooritavad artikli 3 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 3 osutatud kokkuostutehingud, pakkumismenetluse raames toote tarnimiseks FOB- v&otilde;i samav&auml;&auml;rse etapini. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where cereals held by the intervention agencies are used, tenders shall be invited for loading, transportation, processing where necessary and delivery either fob or at a corresponding stage. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kasutatakse sekkumisametite valduses olevat teravilja, kutsutakse &uuml;les tegema pakkumisi selle pealelaadimiseks, veoks, vajaduse korral t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiseks ja tarnimiseks FOB- v&otilde;i samav&auml;&auml;rse etapini. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> When it is decided that cereals will be supplied, under a Community action, at a stage later than either fob or a stage corresponding to fob, the invitation to tender referred to in paragraph 1 or 2 shall cover supply up to that later stage. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui otsustatakse, et teravilja tarnitakse &uuml;henduse meetmena etapini, mis j&auml;rgneb FOB-etapile v&otilde;i FOBiga samav&auml;&auml;rsele etapile, h&otilde;lmab l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 osutatud pakkumismenetlus tarneid kuni k&otilde;nealuse hilisema etapini. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The terms of the invitation to tender must ensure equal access and treatment for all persons concerned irrespective of their place of establishment within the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> Pakkumismenetluse tingimused peavad tagama k&otilde;igi asjaosaliste v&otilde;rdse v&otilde;imaluse menetluses osaleda ja v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise s&otilde;ltumata nende asukohast &uuml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> For a national action, the Member State concerned shall communicate to the Commission the date on which it intends to initiate its action, the financial year against which this would be charged, the proposed intervals between deliveries, the country of destination, the quantity and the product concerned, the port of loading and the envisaged method of mobilization. </inglise>
<eesti> Siseriikliku meetme puhul teatab asjaomane liikmesriik komisjonile kuup&auml;eva, millal ta kavatseb oma meetme algatada, eelarveaasta, kuhu kulu kirjendatakse, kavandatavad ajavahemikud tarnete vahel, sihtriigi, koguse ja asjaomase toote, lastimissadama ja kavandatava varumismeetodi. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> On receipt of this Communication, the Commission shall examine, in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 26 of Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75 or, where appropriate, of Regulation No 359/67/EEC and in the light of the overall situation of the Community market, whether the envisaged method of mobilization meets the conditions referred to in Article 3 and shall suggest if necessary that the Member State concerned modify the envisaged method of mobilization. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle teate saamisel kontrollib komisjon m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 v&otilde;i vastavalt vajadusele m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 359/67/EM&Uuml; artiklis 26 s&auml;testatud korras ning &uuml;henduse turul &uuml;ldist olukorda silmas pidades, kas kavandatav varumismeetod vastab artiklis 3 osutatud tingimustele, ning vajaduse korral soovitab, et asjaomane liikmesriik muudaks kavandatavat varumismeetodit. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> For a Community action, the Commission shall, after considering the market situation and in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 26 of Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75 or, where appropriate, of Regulation No 359/67/EEC, determine the conditions governing mobilization, taking into account in particular the criteria laid down in Article 3. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse meetme puhul m&auml;&auml;rab komisjon p&auml;rast turuolukorra kaalumist m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 v&otilde;i vastavalt vajadusele m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 359/67/EM&Uuml; artiklis 26 s&auml;testatud korras kindlaks varumistingimused, v&otilde;ttes eelk&otilde;ige arvesse artiklis 3 s&auml;testatud tingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of emergency Community actions concerning cereals in the unaltered state, Member States shall hold available for delivery at any time certain quantities of those products which have been taken over by the intervention agency, or else immediately make available the necessary quantities of products drawn from stocks existing on their market if the intervention agency does not have the necessary quantities. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse kriisimeetmete puhul, mis k&auml;sitlevad teravilja muutmata kujul, hoiavad liikmesriigid igal ajal tarnevalmis teatava koguse k&otilde;nealuseid sekkumisameti varutud tooteid v&otilde;i kui sekkumisametil ei ole vajalikke koguseid, teevad nad viivitamata k&auml;ttesaadavaks vajalikud tootekogused oma turul olemasolevatest varudest. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of emergency Community actions concerning the processed cereals referred to in Article 1 and rice other than paddy rice, each Member State designated in accordance with paragraph 4 shall invite tenders by a quick procedure for the supply of the products delivered either fob or at a corresponding stage. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse kriisimeetmete puhul, mis k&auml;sitlevad artiklis 1 osutatud t&ouml;&ouml;deldud teravilja ja riisi, v&auml;lja arvatud koorimata riisi, kutsub iga l&otilde;ike 4 kohaselt m&auml;&auml;ratud liikmesriik tegema kiirmenetluse teel pakkumisi toote tarnimiseks FOB- v&otilde;i samav&auml;&auml;rse etapini. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> To enable products to be transported rapidly from the place where they are held or made available, in the case of the products referred to in paragraph 1, or from the fob or corresponding stage, in the case of the products referred to in paragraph 2, each Member State designated in accordance with paragraph 4 may have recourse to procedures other than the invitation to tender. </inglise>
<eesti> Toodete kiireks transportimiseks l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud toodete puhul nende hoiu- v&otilde;i varumiskohast v&otilde;i l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud toodete puhul FOB-etapist v&otilde;i samav&auml;&auml;rsest etapist on k&otilde;igil l&otilde;ike 4 kohaselt m&auml;&auml;ratud liikmesriikidel &otilde;igus kasutada muid menetlusi kui pakkumismenetlus. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> As soon as the principle of an emergency Community action has been adopted, the Commission shall decide which Member State or States shall be responsible for carrying out the action, fix the date thereof, determine the place where the products must be made available within the Community or within the recipient country, as appropriate, and finally determine any other elements necessary for carrying out this action. </inglise>
<eesti> Niipea kui &uuml;henduse kriisimeetme p&otilde;him&otilde;te on vastu v&otilde;etud, otsustab komisjon, milline liikmesriik v&otilde;i millised liikmesriigid vastutavad meetme rakendamise eest, kinnitab selleks kuup&auml;eva, m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks vastavalt vajadusele kas &uuml;henduse piires v&otilde;i abisaaja riigi piires koha, kus tooted tuleb k&auml;ttesaadavaks teha, ning l&otilde;puks m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks k&otilde;ik muud vajalikud elemendid selle meetme rakendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The quantity and nature of the products referred to in paragraph 1 shall be determined by the Council, acting by qualified majority on a proposal from the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud toodete koguse ja laadi m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks n&otilde;ukogu komisjoni ettepaneku p&otilde;hjal kvalifitseeritud h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> Detailed rules for applying this Article, and in particular the criteria according to which the Commission is to take the decisions referred to in paragraph 4, shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 26 of Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75 or, where appropriate, of Regulation No 359/67/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad k&auml;esoleva artikli kohaldamiseks ning eelk&otilde;ige kriteeriumid, mille kohaselt komisjon teeb l&otilde;ikes 4 osutatud otsused, v&otilde;etakse vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 v&otilde;i vastavalt vajadusele m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 359/67/EM&Uuml; artiklis 26 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Council Regulation (EEC) No 1693/72 (1) of 3 August 1972 fixing criteria for the mobilization of cereals intended as food aid, is hereby repealed. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu 3. augusti 1972. aasta m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 1693/72, (4) millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks toiduabiks etten&auml;htud teravilja varumise kriteeriumid, tunnistatakse kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> References to the Regulation repealed by virtue of paragraph 1 shall be construed as references to this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Viiteid l&otilde;ikega 1 kehtetuks tunnistatud m&auml;&auml;rusele k&auml;sitatakse viidetena k&auml;esolevale m&auml;&auml;rusele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on 1 November 1975. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 1. novembril 1975. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Luxembourg, 29 October 1975. </inglise>
<eesti> Luxembourg, 29. oktoober 1975 N&otilde;ukogu nimel </eesti>
